.TH "xenbus_dev_fatal" 9 "xenbus_dev_fatal" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xenbus_dev_fatal \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" xenbus_dev_fatal
.BI "(struct xenbus_device *dev "  ","
.BI "int err "  ","
.BI "const char *fmt "  ","
.BI "... "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
xenbus device
.IP "err" 12
error to report
.IP "fmt" 12
error message format
.IP "..." 12
variable arguments
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Equivalent to xenbus_dev_error(dev, err, fmt, args), followed by
xenbus_switch_state(dev, XenbusStateClosing) to schedule an orderly
closedown of this driver and its peer.
